45 the funds into the Hurricane Helene Disaster Recovery Fund established in Section 4.1 of S.L.
46 2024-51. The transfer and deposit of funds into reserves pursuant to this section does not
47 constitute an "appropriation made by law," as that phrase is used in Section 7(1) of Article V of
48 the North Carolina Constitution. The funds shall remain unappropriated unless the General
49 Assembly appropriates the funds in this or a subsequent act. In accordance with G.S. 147-69.1(d),
50 funds in the Reserves shall be invested by the Department of the State Treasurer, with earnings
51 and interest therefrom being transferred to and deposited in the General Fund.
