3 (q) Exemptions. – This subsection shall not apply to utilization review requests that are
4 pending review by an insurer or its URO. An insurer may not require a provider to request a
5 utilization review for a healthcare service in order for the covered person to whom the healthcare
6 service is being provided to receive coverage for the service if, within the most recent 12-month
7 period, the insurer or its URO has issued certifications, or would have issued certifications, for
8 not less than eighty percent (80%) of the utilization review requests submitted by the provider
9 for that healthcare service. An insurer may evaluate whether a provider continues to qualify for
10 this exemption not more than once every 12 months. All of the following apply to an exemption
11 under this subsection:
12 (1) A provider is not required to request an exemption in order to qualify for the
13 exemption.
14 (2) No more than once per year per healthcare service, a provider who does not
15 receive an exemption under this subsection may request from the insurer
16 evidence to support the insurer's decision. A healthcare provider may appeal
17 an insurer's decision to deny the exemption.
18 (3) An insurer may only revoke an exemption at the end of the applicable
19 12-month period if the insurer does all of the following:
20 a. Makes a determination that the provider would not have met the eighty
21 percent (80%) approval criteria based on a retrospective review of the
22 claims for the particular service for which the exemption applies for
23 the previous three months or for a longer period if needed to reach a
24 minimum of 10 claims for review.
25 b. Provides the provider with the information the insurer relied upon in
26 making the determination to revoke the exemption.
27 c. Provides the provider a plain language explanation of how to appeal
28 the decision.
29 (4) If an insurer revokes an exemption, then that exemption will remain in effect
30 until the thirtieth calendar day after the date the insurer notifies the provider
31 of its revocation of the exemption unless the provider appeals the revocation.
32 If the provider appeals the revocation, then the exemption shall remain in
33 effect until the fifth calendar day after the revocation is upheld on appeal.
34 (5) An insurer shall provide a healthcare provider that receives an exemption all
35 of the following:
36 a. A statement that the provider qualifies for an exemption from
37 preauthorization requirements.
38 b. A list of services for which the exemption applies.
39 c. A statement of the duration of the exemption.
