10 amended by adding a new section to read:
11 "§ 58-50-64. Utilization review disciplinary actions; North Carolina Medical Board.
12 (a) Performing any portion of the utilization review process under G.S. 58-50-61 that is
13 required to be performed by a licensed physician, including making a final utilization review
14 decision, issuing a noncertification, and participating on behalf of the insurer in the utilization
15 reconsideration and appeal process, is the practice of medicine under G.S. 90-1.1(5).
16 (b) The North Carolina Medical Board has the authority to subpoena an insurer, or a
17 utilization review organization acting on behalf of an insurer, for any records, documents, or
18 other materials pertaining to the involvement of any physician licensed in this State in the
19 utilization review process under G.S. 58-50-61.
20 (c) If an insurer, or a utilization review organization acting on behalf of an insurer, fails
21 to comply with a subpoena issued in accordance with this section, the North Carolina Medical
22 Board shall report the failure to comply and any information supporting the failure to the
23 Commissioner.
24 (d) Notwithstanding the penalty minimum limit under G.S. 58-2-70, the failure of an
25 insurer, or a utilization review organization acting on behalf of an insurer, to provide information
26 required by a subpoena issued in accordance with this section is a violation subjecting the insurer
27 to a fine of no less than five hundred dollars ($500.00) for each 90-day period in which the
28 information is not produced.
29 (e) If the North Carolina Medical Board takes any disciplinary action under G.S. 90-14(a)
30 against a licensed physician as a result of that physician's involvement in the utilization review
31 process under G.S. 58-50-61, then any noncertifications that were issued that are related, in whole
32 or in part, to the disciplinary action shall be subject to reconsideration or appeal under
33 G.S. 58-50-61 so long as the noncertification had not been reversed prior to the disciplinary
34 action. The North Carolina Medical Board shall notify the insurer of the disciplinary action and
