46 SECTION 5.15.(c) Implementation. – Notwithstanding Section 310, Residential
47 Group R, of the North Carolina Building Code, and Section 203.10, Residential Group R, of the
48 North Carolina Fire Code, a family child care home located within a dwelling subject to the North
49 Carolina Building Code shall be treated as a Residential Group R-3 occupancy. The dwelling
50 where the family child care home is located shall be permitted to comply with the North Carolina
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 49

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Building Code, provided that a family child care home must meet only the following additional
2 requirements:
3 (1) Rooms and areas within a family child care home where occupants receive
4 care shall be on the same level of exit discharge.
5 (2) Rooms and areas within a family child care home where occupants receive
6 care shall be located on the same level with, and within a maximum of 40 feet
7 travel distance to, at least one 2A:10B:C fire extinguisher.
