20 "SECTION 4.10.(z) The General Assembly makes the following findings:
21 (1) North Carolina's rural population is among the largest in the United States and
22 is in need of dedicated effort and investment to help improve health outcomes
23 in many of the State's rural communities.
24 (2) The East Carolina University Brody School of Medicine, the University of
25 North Carolina School of Medicine, University Health Systems of Eastern
26 Carolina, Inc., a nonprofit corporation doing business as ECU Health (ECU
27 Health), and the University of North Carolina Health Care System are
28 dedicated to extending and improving health care services and health provider
29 education for the benefit of North Carolina citizens and communities;
30 delivering care close to where citizens live and work; and transforming rural
31 health care for the benefit of North Carolina.
32 "SECTION 4.10.(aa) It is the intent of the General Assembly that ECU Health, UNC Health
33 Care System, and their affiliated schools of medicine (East Carolina University Brody School of
34 Medicine and the University of North Carolina School of Medicine) will collaborate to establish
35 a new initiative to be known as NC Care. The purpose of the NC Care initiative is to improve
36 access to high quality health care for citizens and communities located in rural areas of North
37 Carolina by establishing outcome driven regional systems of care, beginning in eastern North
38 Carolina. To that end, of the funds authorized in this act or appropriated in this act to the Board
39 of Governors of The University of North Carolina over the 2023-2025 fiscal biennium, a total of
40 four hundred twenty fifty million dollars ($420,000,000) ($50,000,000) is provided for
41 investment in the NC Care initiative as follows:
42 (1) The sum of ten million dollars ($10,000,000) for Clinically Integrated
43 Network.
44 (2) The sum of two hundred ten million dollars ($210,000,000) for three health
45 clinics, of which the sum of one hundred five million dollars ($105,000,000)
46 has been appropriated.
47 (3) The sum of one hundred fifty million dollars ($150,000,000) for hospital
48 investment.
49 (4) The sum of fifty million dollars ($50,000,000) for a regional behavioral health
50 facility.
