17 (y) The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy to be applied uniformly
18 throughout the Community College System to provide that any student enrolled in a community
19 college who is a National Guard service member placed onto State active duty status during an
20 academic term shall be given an excused absence for the period of time the student is on active
21 duty. The policy shall further provide all of the following:
22 (1) The student shall be given the opportunity to make up any test or other work
23 missed during the excused absence.
24 (2) The student shall be given the option, when feasible, to continue classes and
25 coursework during the academic term through online participation for the
26 period of time the student is placed on active duty.
27 (3) The student shall be given the option of receiving a temporary grade of
28 "incomplete (IN)" or "absent from the final exam (AB)" for any course that
29 the student was unable to complete as a result of being placed on State active
30 duty status; however, the student must complete the course requirements
31 within the period of time specified by the community college to avoid
32 receiving a failing grade for the course.
33 (4) The student shall be permitted to drop, with no penalty, any course that the
34 student was unable to complete as a result of being placed on State active duty
35 status.
36 (z) The State Board of Community Colleges shall monitor community colleges for
37 compliance with Article 38 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes. If the State Board determines
38 that a community college is in violation of Article 38, it shall report the identity of the community
39 college to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee.
40 "§ 115D-5.1. Workforce Development Programs.
41 (a) Community colleges shall assist in the preemployment and in-service training of
42 employees in industry, business, agriculture, health occupation and governmental agencies. Such
43 training shall include instruction on worker safety and health standards and practices applicable
44 to the field of employment. The State Board of Community Colleges shall make appropriate
45 regulations including the establishment of maximum hours of instruction which may be offered
46 at State expense in each in-plant training program. No instructor or other employee of a
47 community college shall engage in the normal management, supervisory and operational
48 functions of the establishment in which the instruction is offered during the hours in which the
49 instructor or other employee is employed for instructional or educational purposes.
