14 each year to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee on:
15 (1) The total amount of funds received by a company under the Customized
16 Training Program.
17 (1a) The types of services sought by the company, whether for new, expanding, or
18 existing industry.
19 (2) The amount of funds per trainee received by that company.
20 (3) The amount of funds received per trainee by the community college delivering
21 the training.
22 (4) The number of trainees trained by the company and community college.
23 (5) The number of years that company has been funded.
24 (f1) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the State Board of Community Colleges
25 may adopt guidelines that allow the Customized Training Program to use funds appropriated for
26 that program to support training projects for the various branches of the Armed Forces of the
27 United States.
28 (f2) Funds available to the Customized Training Program shall not revert at the end of a
29 fiscal year but shall remain available until expended. Up to ten percent (10%) of the
30 college-delivered training expenditures and up to five percent (5%) of the contractor-delivered
31 training expenditures for the prior fiscal year for Customized Training may be allotted to each
32 college for capacity building at that college.
33 (f3) Of the funds appropriated in a fiscal year for the Customized Training Programs, the
34 State Board of Community Colleges may approve the use of up to eight percent (8%) for the
35 training and support of regional community college personnel to deliver Customized Training
36 Program services to business and industry.
37 (g) The State Board shall adopt guidelines to implement this section. At least 20 days
38 before the effective date of any criteria or nontechnical amendments to guidelines, the State
