48 "§ 115D-5.1A. Short-Term Workforce Development Grant Program.
49 (a) Program Established. – There is established the North Carolina Community College
50 Short-Term Workforce Development Grant Program (Program) to be administered by the State
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 69

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Board of Community Colleges. The State Board shall adopt rules for the disbursement of the
2 grants pursuant to this section.
3 (b) Programs of Study. – The State Board of Community Colleges, in collaboration with
4 the Department of Commerce, shall determine the eligible programs of study for the Program,
5 according to the occupations that are in the highest demand in the State. The eligible programs
6 of study shall include programs such as architecture and construction, health sciences,
7 information technology, electrical line worker, and manufacturing programs and may include
8 other programs to meet local workforce needs.
9 (c) Award Amounts. – To the extent funds are made available for the Program, the State
10 Board of Community Colleges shall award grants in an amount of up to seven hundred fifty
11 dollars ($750.00) to students pursuing short-term, noncredit State and industry workforce
12 credentials. The State Board of Community Colleges shall establish criteria for initial and
13 continuing eligibility for students. At a minimum, students shall be required to qualify as a
14 resident for tuition purposes under the criteria set forth in G.S. 116-143.1 and in accordance with
15 the coordinated and centralized residency determination process administered by the State
16 Education Assistance Authority.
17 (d) Report. – The State Board shall submit a report by April 1, 2024, and annually
18 thereafter, on the Program to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee and the Fiscal
19 Research Division. The report shall contain, for each academic year and by programs of study,
20 the amount of grant funds disbursed and the number of eligible students receiving funds.
