42 "§ 115D-6.1. Administration of institutions.
43 (a) Policies. – The State Board of Community Colleges may adopt and execute such
44 policies, regulations, and standards concerning the establishment, administration, and operation
45 of institutions as the State Board may deem necessary to ensure the quality of educational
46 programs, to promote the systematic meeting of educational needs of the State, and to provide
47 for the equitable distribution of State and federal funds to the several institutions.
48 (b) Authority. – The State Board shall have the following authority with respect to
49 individual institutions:
50 (1) To approve sites, capital improvement projects, and budgets.
51 (2) To approve the selection of the chief administrative officer.
