17 "§ 115D-10.65. Accreditation of secondary school located in North Carolina shall not be a
18 factor in admissions, loans, scholarships, or other educational policies.
19 (a) For purposes of this section, the term "accreditation" shall include certification or any
20 other similar approval process.
21 (b) The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy that prohibits any
22 community college from soliciting or using information regarding the accreditation of a
23 secondary school located in North Carolina that a person attended as a factor affecting
24 admissions, loans, scholarships, or other educational activity at the community college, unless
25 the accreditation was conducted by a State agency.
26 "§ 115D-10.70. Driving eligibility certificates.
27 (a) The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt the following rules to assist
28 community colleges in their administration of procedures necessary to implement G.S. 20-11 and
29 G.S. 20-13.2:
30 (1) To establish the procedures a person who is or was enrolled in a community
31 college must follow and the requirements that person must meet to obtain a
32 driving eligibility certificate.
33 (2) To require the person who is required under G.S. 20-11(n) to sign the driving
34 eligibility certificate to provide the certificate if he or she determines that one
35 of the following requirements is met:
36 a. The person seeking the certificate is eligible for the certificate under
37 G.S. 20-11(n)(1) and is not subject to G.S. 20-11(n1).
38 b. The person seeking the certificate is eligible for the certificate under
39 G.S. 20-11(n)(1) and G.S. 20-11(n1).
40 (3) To provide for an appeal through the grievance procedures established by the
41 board of trustees of each community college by a person who is denied a
42 driving eligibility certificate.
43 (4) To define exemplary student behavior and to define what constitutes the
44 successful completion of a drug or alcohol treatment counseling program.
45 (b) The State Board shall develop policies as to when it is appropriate to notify the
46 Division of Motor Vehicles that a person who is or was enrolled in a community college no
47 longer meets the requirements for a driving eligibility certificate. The State Board also shall adopt
48 guidelines to assist the presidents of community colleges in their designation of representatives
49 to sign driving eligibility certificates.
50 (c) The State Board shall develop a form for the appropriate individuals to provide their
51 written, irrevocable consent for a community college to disclose to the Division of Motor
Page 78 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Vehicles that the student no longer meets the conditions for a driving eligibility certificate under
2 G.S. 20-11(n)(1) or G.S. 20-11(n1), if applicable, in the event that this disclosure is necessary to
3 comply with G.S. 20-11 or G.S. 20-13.2. Other than identifying under which statutory subsection
4 the student is no longer eligible, no other details or information concerning the student's school
5 record shall be released pursuant to this consent.
6 "§ 115D-10.75. Excused absences for religious observances.
7 The State Board of Community Colleges shall direct each community college to adopt a
8 policy that authorizes a minimum of two excused absences each academic year for religious
9 observances required by the faith of a student. The policy may require that the student provide
10 written notice of the request for an excused absence a reasonable time prior to the religious
11 observance. The policy shall also provide that the student shall be given the opportunity to make
12 up any tests or other work missed due to an excused absence for a religious observance.
13 "§ 115D-10.76. Excused absences for National Guard service members.
14 The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy to be applied uniformly
15 throughout the Community College System to provide that any student enrolled in a community
16 college who is a National Guard service member placed onto State active duty status during an
17 academic term shall be given an excused absence for the period of time the student is on active
18 duty. The policy shall further provide all of the following:
19 (1) The student shall be given the opportunity to make up any test or other work
20 missed during the excused absence.
21 (2) The student shall be given the option, when feasible, to continue classes and
22 coursework during the academic term through online participation for the
23 period of time the student is placed on active duty.
24 (3) The student shall be given the option of receiving a temporary grade of
25 "incomplete (IN)" or "absent from the final exam (AB)" for any course that
26 the student was unable to complete as a result of being placed on State active
27 duty status; however, the student must complete the course requirements
28 within the period of time specified by the community college to avoid
29 receiving a failing grade for the course.
30 (4) The student shall be permitted to drop, with no penalty, any course that the
31 student was unable to complete as a result of being placed on State active duty
32 status."
