44 SECTION 6.5.(c) Article 2 of Chapter 115D of the General Statutes is amended by
45 adding a new section to read:
46 "§ 115D-21.2. Accreditation.
47 (a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
48 (1) Accreditation cycle. – The period of time during which a community college
49 is accredited.
50 (2) Accrediting agency. – An agency or association that accredits institutions of
51 higher education.
Page 80 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (3) Regional accrediting agency. – One of the following accrediting agencies:
2 a. Higher Learning Commission.
3 b. Middle States Commission on Higher Education.
4 c. New England Commission on Higher Education.
5 d. Northwest Commission on Colleges and Universities.
6 e. Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on
7 Colleges.
8 f. Western Association of Schools and Colleges Accrediting
9 Commission for Community and Junior Colleges.
10 (b) Prohibit Consecutive Accreditation by an Accrediting Agency. – A community
11 college shall not receive accreditation by an accrediting agency for consecutive accreditation
12 cycles except as provided in subsection (c) of this section.
13 (c) Accreditation Transfer Procedure. – A community college that pursues accreditation
14 with a different accrediting agency in accordance with this section shall pursue accreditation with
15 a regional accrediting agency. If the community college is not granted candidacy status by any
16 regional accrediting agency that is different from its current accrediting agency at least three
17 years prior to the expiration of its current accreditation, the community college may remain with
18 its current accrediting agency for an additional accreditation cycle.
19 (d) Certain Programs Exempt. – The requirements of this section do not apply to
20 professional, departmental, or certificate programs at community colleges that have specific
21 accreditation requirements or best practices, as identified by the State Board of Community
22 Colleges.
23 (e) Cause of Action. – A community college may bring a civil action, as follows:
24 (1) Against any person who makes a false statement to the accrediting agency of
25 the community college, if all of the following criteria are met:
26 a. The statement, if true, would mean the community college is out of
27 compliance with its accreditation standards.
28 b. The person made the statement with knowledge that the statement was
29 false or with reckless disregard as to whether it was false.
30 c. The accrediting agency conducted a review of the community college
31 as a proximate result of the statement.
32 d. The review caused the community college to incur costs.
33 (2) A community college that prevails on a cause of action initiated pursuant to
34 this subsection shall be entitled to the following:
35 a. Costs related to the review conducted by the accrediting agency,
36 including for the following:
37 1. Additional hours worked by community college personnel.
38 2. Contracted services, including outside legal counsel.
39 3. Travel, lodging, and food expenses.
40 4. Fees required by the agency.
41 b. Reasonable attorneys' fees.
42 c. Court costs."
43 SECTION 6.5.(d) G.S. 115D-21.5 is repealed.
