46 "§ 115D-21.10. Curriculum courses taught throughout year.
47 Community colleges may teach curriculum courses at any time during the year, including the
48 summer term. Student membership hours from these courses shall be counted when computing
49 full-time equivalent students (FTE) for use in budget funding formulas at the State level."
