35 "§ 115D-30.20. Gateway to College Program.
36 The purpose of the first semester of the Gateway to College Program is to address additional
37 support to successfully complete the Program. Students may need to take developmental courses
38 necessary for the transition to more challenging courses; therefore, the State Board of Community
39 Colleges shall (i) permit high school students who are enrolled in Gateway to College Programs
40 to enroll in developmental courses based on an assessment of their individual student needs by a
41 high school and community college staff team and (ii) include this coursework in computing the
42 budget FTE for the colleges.
43 "§ 115D-30.25. NC Career Coach Program.
44 (a) Purpose. – There is established the NC Career Coach Program to place community
45 college career coaches in high schools to assist students with determining career goals and
46 identifying community college programs that would enable students to achieve these goals.
47 (b) Memorandum of Understanding. – The board of trustees of a community college and
48 a local board of education of a local school administrative unit within the service area of the
49 community college shall enter into a memorandum of understanding for the placement of career
50 coaches employed by the board of trustees of the community college in schools within the local
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 83

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 school administrative unit. At a minimum, the memorandum of understanding shall include the
2 following:
3 (1) Requirement that the community college provides the following:
4 a. Hiring, training, and supervision of career coaches. The board of
5 trustees may include a local board of education liaison on the hiring
6 committee to participate in the decision making regarding hiring for
7 the coach positions.
8 b. Salary, benefits, and all other expenses related to the employment of
9 the career coach. The coach will be an employee of the board of
10 trustees and will not be an agent or employee of the local board of
11 education.
12 c. Development of pedagogical materials and technologies needed to
13 enhance the advising process.
14 d. Criminal background checks required by the local school
15 administrative unit for employees working directly with students.
16 e. Agreement that, while on any school campus, the career coach will
17 obey all local board of education rules and will be subject to the
18 authority of the school building administration.
19 (2) Requirement that the local school administrative unit provides the following
20 to career coaches:
21 a. Access to student records, as needed to carry out the coach's job
22 responsibilities.
23 b. Office space on site appropriate for student advising.
24 c. Information technology resources, including, but not limited to,
25 internet access, telephone, and copying.
26 d. Initial school orientation and ongoing integration into the faculty and
27 staff community.
28 e. Promotion of school-wide awareness of coach duties.
29 f. Facilitation of the coach's access to individual classes and larger
30 assemblies for the purposes of awareness building.
31 (c) Application for NC Career Coach Program Funding. – The board of trustees of a
32 community college and a local board of education of a local school administrative unit within the
33 service area of the community college jointly may apply for available funds for NC Career Coach
34 Program funding from the State Board of Community Colleges. The State Board of Community
35 Colleges shall establish a process for award of funds as follows:
36 (1) Advisory committee. – Establishment of an advisory committee, which shall
37 include representatives from the NC Community College System, the
38 Department of Public Instruction, the Department of Commerce, and at least
39 three representatives of the business community, to review applications and
40 make recommendations for funding awards to the State Board.
41 (2) Application submission requirements. – The State Board of Community
42 Colleges shall require at least the following:
43 a. Evidence of a signed memorandum of understanding that meets, at a
44 minimum, the requirements of this section.
45 b. Evidence that the funding request will be matched with local funds in
46 accordance with the following:
47 1. Matching funds may come from public or private sources.
48 2. The match amount shall be determined based on the
49 development tier designation of the county in which the local
50 school administrative unit is located where the career coach is
