6 "§ 115D-39.5. Tuition waivers.
7 (a) Allowed Tuition Waivers. – The State Board of Community Colleges shall not waive
8 tuition and registration fees for any individuals, except the State Board may, as provided by
9 general and uniform regulations, waive tuition and registration fees for the following:
10 (1) Persons not enrolled in elementary or secondary schools taking courses
11 leading to a high school diploma or equivalent certificate.
12 (2) Courses requested by the following entities that support the organizations'
13 training needs and are on a specialized course list approved by the State Board:
14 a. Volunteer fire departments.
15 b. Municipal, county, or State fire departments.
16 c. Volunteer EMS or rescue and lifesaving departments.
17 d. Municipal, county, or State EMS or rescue and lifesaving departments.
18 e. Law enforcement, fire, or EMS or rescue and lifesaving entities
19 serving a lake authority that was created by a county board of
20 commissioners prior to July 1, 2012.
21 f. Radio Emergency Associated Communications Teams (REACT)
22 under contract to a county as an emergency response agency.
23 g. Municipal, county, or State law enforcement agencies.
24 h. Campus police agencies of private institutions of higher education
25 certified by the Attorney General pursuant to Chapter 74G of the
26 General Statutes.
27 i. The Division of Prisons of the Department of Adult Correction and the
28 Division of Juvenile Justice of the Department of Public Safety for the
29 training of full-time custodial employees and employees of the
30 Divisions required to be certified under Article 1 of Chapter 17C of
31 the General Statutes and the rules of the Criminal Justice and Training
32 Standards Commission.
33 j. The Eastern Band of Cherokee Indians law enforcement, fire, or EMS
34 or rescue and lifesaving tribal government departments or programs.
35 k. The Criminal Justice Standards Division of the Department of Justice
36 for the training of criminal justice professionals who are required to be
37 certified under (i) Article 1 of Chapter 17C of the General Statutes and
38 the rules of the North Carolina Criminal Justice Education and
39 Training Standards Commission or (ii) Chapter 17E of the General
40 Statutes and the rules of the North Carolina Sheriffs' Education and
41 Training Standards Commission. The waivers provided for in this
42 sub-subdivision apply to participants and recent graduates of the North
43 Carolina Criminal Justice Fellows Program to obtain certifications for
44 eligible criminal justice professions, as defined in G.S. 17C-20(6).
45 (3) Firefighters, EMS personnel, and rescue and lifesaving personnel whose duty
46 station is located on a military installation within North Carolina for courses
47 that support their organizations' training needs and are approved for this
48 purpose by the State Board.
49 (4) Trainees enrolled in courses conducted under the Customized Training
50 Program.
