6 FISCAL RESPONSIBILITY AND COMMUNITY COLLEGE TECH PLANNING
7 SECTION 6.7. Chapter 115D of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
8 section to read:
9 "§ 115D-9.40. Evaluation of technology costs.
10 The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy that requires all community
11 colleges to evaluate the following when acquiring technology, computer hardware, and software:
12 (1) The long-term cost of ownership, including costs of repairing the technology,
13 computer hardware, or software.
14 (2) Any flexibility for innovation during the life of the technology, computer
15 hardware, or software.
16 (3) Any anticipated resale or salvage value at the end of the target life cycle for
17 the technology, computer hardware, or software based on the average resale
18 or salvage value of similar technology, computer hardware, or software as a
19 percentage of the initial cost of purchase."
20
21 EXPEDITED TEACHER PIPELINE PATHWAY STUDY
22 SECTION 6.8. No later than March 15, 2026, ApprenticeshipNC shall report to the
23 Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee on a plan to facilitate one or more expedited
24 pathways for apprenticeship candidates to enter the teaching profession. ApprenticeshipNC shall
25 develop the plan in collaboration with the Board of Governors of The University of North
26 Carolina, the State Board of Community Colleges, the Department of Public Instruction, and
27 Teach NC. In addition, ApprenticeshipNC may, in its discretion, collaborate with representatives
28 of approved educator preparation programs, local school administrative units, and existing
29 apprenticeship programs. The plan shall include at least the following components:
30 (1) Options for an accelerated transition pathway that allows high school students
31 to earn college credits leading to a teaching license while participating in
32 structured, paid, or other experiential learning in the classroom, including
33 applicable program design and sequencing components needed to achieve that
34 goal.
35 (2) Maximize usage and transferability of at least the following coursework
36 completion opportunities:
37 a. College transfer pathways provided through the Career and College
38 Promise Program that support entry into a recognized educator
39 preparation program.
40 b. Community college coursework leading to completion of an associate
41 degree related to teacher preparation.
42 c. Online or asynchronous coursework provided at a constituent
43 institution of The University of North Carolina leading to a bachelor's
44 degree.
45 d. Enrollment in an associate degree program or a bachelor's degree
46 program while serving (i) as a full-time employee in a public school
47 unit and (ii) as a teacher assistant or apprentice in a registered
48 apprenticeship program pursuant to G.S. 115C-269.33, as enacted by
49 Section 7.37 of this act.
50 (3) Any legislative changes or appropriations needed to implement the plan.
51
