41 DIGITAL CREDENTIAL PILOT PROGRAM
42 SECTION 6.11.(a) There is established the Digital Credential Pilot Program
43 (Program) for the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium. The purpose of the Program is to evaluate the
44 effectiveness of digital credential vaults for use by community college students. The North
45 Carolina Community Colleges System Office shall contract with a third-party entity to create a
46 secure, interoperable digital vault platform capable of issuing, storing, verifying, and sharing
47 learner credentials, including microcredentials, certifications, transcripts, and verified skill
48 records and credentials. The platform shall provide equitable cross-device access for learners and
49 allow for credential portability across educational institutions and employers, support open
50 standards for interoperability, offer real-time verification, and ensure privacy and security in
51 compliance with applicable laws. The system shall enable learners to manage a comprehensive,
Page 96 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 lifelong record of achievement that is accessible, verifiable, and shareable with third parties
2 through digital means. Vault data must be user-encrypted to prevent unauthorized access or sale,
3 and all credential and learner data shall be owned and controlled by the student.
4 SECTION 6.11.(b) The System Office shall select six community colleges to
5 participate in the Program. The System Office shall make an application available to all
6 community colleges for participation in the Program no later than 30 days after this section
7 becomes law. Community colleges may submit applications up to 30 days after the application
8 is made available. The System Office shall select community colleges to participate in the
9 Program no later than 30 days after the close of the application window.
10 SECTION 6.11.(c) The System Office shall conduct a study on the efficacy of
11 raising student fees to continue the Program beyond the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium. The System
12 Office shall report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee on the results of the
13 study by January 15, 2027.
