37 qualifications of mentor teachers and a schedule of supervision.
38 (3) Alternative sources of funding to support apprenticeships that could be paired
39 with State funds received under the Program, including federal workforce
40 development funds.
41 (4) An explanation of how the unit would incorporate its registered teacher
42 apprenticeship program with its advanced teaching roles program to enhance
43 the learning environment for apprentices.
44 (5) Strategies to encourage candidates to accept an apprenticeship instead of
45 directly entering the teacher profession on a Residency License, Emergency
46 License, or permit to teach.
47 (d) Selection of Recipients. – By March 15 of each school year in which proposals are
48 submitted, ApprenticeshipNC shall review the proposals and select local school administrative
49 units to participate in the Program, beginning in the subsequent school year. ApprenticeshipNC
