9 "Part 6. Grants for CTE Homebuilding Programs.
10 "§ 115C-173.20. Grant program established; purpose; use of funds.
11 There is established the CTE Homebuilding Grant Program to provide grants to assist public
12 school units with curriculum costs associated with CTE programs related to the U.S. Department
13 of Labor approved Pre-Apprenticeship Certificate Training (PACT) program developed by the
14 Home Builders Institute. The Department of Public Instruction shall permit high schools within
15 public school units to use the PACT program as an approved curriculum for CTE programs. A
16 public school unit or a regional partnership of more than one public school unit may apply to
17 receive funds. When awarding grants under this Part, the Department shall prioritize public
18 school units (i) located, in whole or in part, in a county with at least one local school
19 administrative unit that received low-wealth supplemental funding in the previous fiscal year and
20 (ii) that have a high population of at-risk students or students with disabilities.
21 "§ 115C-173.21. Application.
22 The Department shall create and make available to all public school units an application for
23 grants under this Part no later than July 15 of each year that funds are made available for this
24 purpose. Applicants shall submit their application to receive grant funds to the Department no
25 later than 60 days after the application is made available. The Department shall approve or deny
26 each application within 30 days of receipt by the Department.
27 "§ 115C-173.24. Reporting.
28 All recipients of grants under this Part shall submit a report to the Department on the
29 outcomes of any programs funded by grants received pursuant to this Part no later than October
30 15 of each year that funds are received, including data collection methods for reporting on student
31 outcomes, impacts of the program, and use of State funds. The Department shall then submit a
32 report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee and the Fiscal Research Division
33 on the overall outcomes of the grant programs no later than December 15 of each year that funds
34 are made available for this purpose."
