3 SECTION 7.44.(a) G.S. 115C-47 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
4 "(70) To Adopt an Internet Safety Policy. – Local boards of education shall adopt
5 policies for student access to the internet provided by the local school
6 administrative unit. The policies shall do at least the following:
7 a. Limit access by students to only age-appropriate subject matter and
8 materials.
9 b. Protect the safety and security of students when accessing email, chat
10 rooms, and other forms of electronic communication.
11 c. Prohibit access by students to data or information maintained by the
12 local school administrative unit, including by "hacking" and other
13 unlawful online activities.
14 d. Prevent access to websites, web applications, or software that does not
15 protect against the disclosure, use, or dissemination of a student's
16 personal information.
17 e. Prohibit and prevent students from accessing social media platforms
18 through the use of internet access provided by the local school
19 administrative unit, except when expressly directed by a teacher solely
20 for educational purposes."
21 SECTION 7.44.(b) Part 1 of Article 8 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is
22 amended by adding a new section to read:
23 "§ 115C-81.26. Social media and mental health.
24 Each local board of education shall provide instruction on social media and its effects on
25 health, including social, emotional, and physical effects. Instruction shall be provided once
26 during elementary school, once during middle school, and twice during high school. Instruction
27 may be included as part of the mental and emotional health instruction provided pursuant to
28 G.S. 115C-81.25. Instruction on this topic shall include at least the following:
29 (1) Negative effects of social media on mental health, including addiction.
30 (2) The distribution of misinformation on social media.
31 (3) Methods of manipulating behavior using social media.
32 (4) The permanency of information shared online.
33 (5) How to maintain personal security.
34 (6) How to identify cyberbullying, predatory behavior, and human trafficking on
35 the internet.
36 (7) How to report suspicious behavior encountered on the internet.
37 (8) Personal and interpersonal skills or character education that enhances
38 individual level protective factors and mitigates or reduces risk-taking or
39 harmful behavior."
