43 CAREER DEVELOPMENT ADJUSTMENT
44 SECTION 7.45.(a) Pilot Program Established; Purpose. – The Superintendent of
45 Public Instruction shall create an Annual Career Development Plan Pilot Program (Program) for
46 students entering the seventh grade at select schools during the 2025-2026 and 2026-2027 school
47 years and continuing through the students' graduation from high school. The purpose of the
48 Program shall be to evaluate the efficacy of reviewing Career Development Plans (Plans)
49 annually to better align students for on-time graduation and achievement of college and career
50 goals and to ensure that all students graduate from high school college or career ready.
51 SECTION 7.45.(b) Definitions. – The following definitions apply to this section:
Page 126 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Career Development Plan. – An individual plan created by each student that
2 establishes the student's plan throughout middle and high school for
3 graduation and career development pursuant to G.S. 115C-158.10.
4 (2) Local board of education. – A local board of education governing a partnered
5 school.
6 (3) Parent. – Defined in G.S. 115C-76.1.
7 (4) Partnered school. – A middle school and high school governed by a local
8 board of education where at least half of the student population of the middle
9 school is assigned to attend the associated high school.
10 SECTION 7.45.(c) Partnered Schools. – The Superintendent shall select 12
11 partnered schools that are proportionally representative of the population size and geographic
12 distribution of public high schools in the State. The Superintendent shall provide a process for
13 schools to apply to participate in the Program as partnered schools. The Superintendent shall be
14 responsible for the final selection of partnered schools. In the event that there are fewer than 12
15 applicants, the Superintendent shall collaborate with local superintendents to select schools to be
16 partnered schools. Partnered schools shall have each student entering the seventh grade during
17 the 2025-2026 and 2026-2027 school years complete an annual review of Plans.
18 SECTION 7.45.(d) Local Board of Education and IEP Support. – The local board
19 of education shall ensure that students in partnered schools are provided assistance by a school
20 counselor and planning time during the instructional day each school year to update their Plans.
21 For students with disabilities, the student's IEP team, if applicable, may assist the student in
22 completing and updating the Plan. Updates to Plans shall be made prior to student scheduling of
23 courses for the next school year.
24 SECTION 7.45.(e) Parental Involvement. – Partnered schools shall encourage
25 parents to participate in development of Plans with their students and to sign a form provided by
26 the school acknowledging the annual revisions of the Plans. Local boards of education shall
27 ensure that Plans are easily accessible to students and parents and shall provide parents annual
28 written notice of the creation or revision of a Plan, information on how to access the Plan, a
29 listing of course offerings for the next school year with a description of the content of each course,
30 and high school graduation requirements where appropriate. Prior to creating or updating a
31 student's Plan, a school counselor shall attempt to meet with the student's parent, either in person
32 or virtually, to explain the possible effects that the Plan might have on the student's graduation
33 requirements and career development planning. Beginning in the tenth grade and continuing
34 throughout the student's high school enrollment, a school counselor shall provide each student
35 and parent information regarding State and federal need-based and merit-based financial aid
36 programs to support postsecondary education and training using information provided by the
37 State Education Assistance Authority and College Foundation of North Carolina. The school
38 counselor shall also provide information on the free application for federal student aid (FAFSA),
39 its use, and notify the parent that information included in the FAFSA is confidential and not
40 accessible by the school.
41 SECTION 7.45.(f) Initial Career Development Plans. – Students in seventh grade in
42 partnered schools shall develop an initial career development plan which will provide guidance
43 as students develop Plans.
44 SECTION 7.45.(g) Annual Career Development Plan Updates. – In partnered
45 schools, Plans shall be updated annually in addition to the following information being provided
46 to students:
47 (1) For eighth grade students, by the end of the school year, a list of the required
48 core courses to be taken in ninth and tenth grades.
49 (2) For tenth grade students, an identification of the graduation requirements
50 relevant to the student's chosen postsecondary goals based on the student's
51 career development planning.
