17 "§ 115C-270.44. Active Military Members or their spouses.
18 A Licensee who is an Active Military Member or is the spouse of an Active Military Member
19 shall be deemed to hold a Home State License in any of the following locations:
20 (1) The Licensee's permanent residence.
21 (2) A Member State that is the Licensee's primary state of practice.
22 (3) A Member State where the Licensee has relocated pursuant to a Permanent
23 Change of Station (PCS).
24 "§ 115C-270.45. Discipline/adverse actions.
25 (a) Nothing in this Compact shall be deemed or construed to limit the authority of a
26 Member State to investigate or impose disciplinary measures on Licensees according to the State
27 Practice Laws thereof.
28 (b) Member States shall be authorized to receive, and shall provide, files and information
29 regarding the investigation and discipline, if any, of Licensees in other Member States upon
30 request. Any Member State receiving such information or files shall protect and maintain the
31 security and confidentiality thereof, in at least the same manner that it maintains its own
32 investigatory or disciplinary files and information. Prior to disclosing any disciplinary or
33 investigatory information received from another Member State, the disclosing state shall
34 communicate its intention and purpose for such disclosure to the Member State which originally
35 provided that information.
36 "§ 115C-270.46. Establishment of the School Psychologist Interstate Licensure Compact
37 Commission.
38 (a) The Member States hereby create and establish a joint government agency whose
39 membership consists of all Member States that have enacted the Compact, and this agency shall
40 be known as the School Psychologist Interstate Licensure Compact Commission. The
41 Commission is an instrumentality of the Member States acting jointly and not an instrumentality
42 of any one state. The Commission shall come into existence on or after the effective date of the
43 Compact as set forth in G.S. 115C-270.50.
44 (b) Membership, Voting, and Meetings.
45 (1) Each Member State shall have and be limited to one delegate selected by that
46 Member State's State Licensing Authority.
47 (2) The delegate shall be the primary administrative officer of the Member State
48 Licensing Authority or their designee who is an employee of the Member
49 State Licensing Authority.
50 (3) The Commission shall by Rule or bylaw establish a term of office for
51 delegates and may by Rule or bylaw establish term limits.
