19 "§ 115C-270.47. Facilitating information exchange.
20 (a) The Commission shall provide for facilitating the exchange of information to
21 administer and implement the provisions of this Compact in accordance with the Rules of the
22 Commission, consistent with generally accepted data protection principles.
23 (b) Notwithstanding any other provision of state law to the contrary, a Member State shall
24 agree to provide for the facilitation of the following Licensee information as required by the
25 Rules of the Commission, including:
26 (1) Identifying information.
27 (2) Licensure data.
28 (3) Adverse Actions against a Licensee and information related thereto.
29 (4) Nonconfidential information related to Alternative Program participation, the
30 beginning and ending dates of such participation, and other information
31 related to such participation not made confidential under Member State law.
32 (5) Any denial of application for licensure, and the reason(s) for such denial.
33 (6) The presence of investigative information.
34 (7) Other information that may facilitate the administration of this Compact or the
35 protection of the public, as determined by the Rules of the Commission.
36 (c) Nothing in this Compact shall be deemed or construed to alter, limit, or inhibit the
37 power of a Member State to control and maintain ownership of its Licensee information or alter,
38 limit, or inhibit the laws or regulations governing Licensee information in the Member State.
39 "§ 115C-270.48. Rulemaking.
40 (a) The Commission shall exercise its Rulemaking powers pursuant to the criteria set
41 forth in this interstate compact and the Rules adopted thereunder. Rules and amendments shall
42 become binding as of the date specified in each Rule or amendment.
43 (b) The Commission shall promulgate reasonable Rules to achieve the intent and purpose
44 of this interstate compact. In the event the Commission exercises its Rulemaking authority in a
45 manner that is beyond the purpose and intent of this interstate compact, or the powers granted
46 hereunder, then such an action by the Commission shall be invalid and have no force and effect
47 of law in the Member States.
48 (c) If a majority of the legislatures of the Member States reject a Rule, by enactment of a
49 statute or resolution in the same manner used to adopt the Compact within four years of the date
50 of adoption of the Rule, then such Rule shall have no further force and effect in any Member
51 State.
