11 COMPETITIVE SPEECH AND DEBATE GRANT PILOT
12 SECTION 7.54.(a) Program; Purpose. – To the extent funds are made available for
13 the purpose, there is established the Competitive Speech and Debate Team Grant Pilot Program
14 (Program). The purpose of the Program is to allow each public school serving students in grades
15 nine through 12 in North Carolina to form a speech and debate team and to allow the team to
16 participate in speech and debate competitions. The Program shall begin in the 2025-2026 school
17 year and conclude at the end of the 2028-2029 school year.
18 SECTION 7.54.(b) Eligibility. – Any public school unit that includes a school that
19 serves students in grades nine through 12 is eligible to apply to the Department of Public
20 Instruction for a grant to develop, maintain, or expand an educational and competitive speech
21 and debate team.
22 SECTION 7.54.(c) Applications; Criteria and Guidelines. – No later than August 1
23 of each year that funds are made available for the Program, the Department shall develop and
24 publish criteria and guidelines for the application process for the Program in the upcoming school
25 year. The Department shall accept applications until September 30 of each school year.
26 Applications shall include, at a minimum, a proposed budget for the speech and debate team.
27 SECTION 7.54.(d) Award; Use of Funds. – The Department shall award grants to
28 selected applicants by October 31 of each year that funds are made available for the Program.
29 The Department shall determine the amount of each award up to a maximum of ten thousand
30 dollars ($10,000) per team per school year and may only include two stipends, one lead team
31 coach stipend of up to two thousand five hundred dollars ($2,500) and one assistant team coach
32 stipend of one thousand five hundred dollars ($1,500). Funds may be used for any of the
33 following purposes:
34 (1) Provide stipends for coaches.
35 (2) Make payments associated with participation in a speech and debate league or
36 competition.
37 (3) Travel to and from speech and debate competitions.
38 SECTION 7.54.(e) Speech and debate teams receiving funds through the Program
39 shall participate in the Tarheel Forensic League and the National Speech and Debate Association.
40 SECTION 7.54.(f) Student Participation. – If a student is enrolled in a school that
41 does not offer a speech and debate team, the student is eligible to participate on the speech and
42 debate team at the school located geographically closest to where the student resides that does
43 have a team. A student joining a team under the authority of this section shall be responsible for
44 transportation to and from the school where the team meets. Nothing in this section prohibits a
45 school from enforcing guidelines for student participation in extracurricular activities, such as
46 academic performance requirements, nor does it prohibit a speech and debate team from
47 conducting a selection process for the team, so long as the student is able to participate in the
48 selection process as if the student were enrolled in that school.
49 SECTION 7.54.(g) Reporting. – No later than February 15 of each school year in
50 which funds are made available for the Program, the Department shall report the following
Page 146 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 information to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee and the Fiscal Research
2 Division:
3 (1) The public school units receiving grants and the amount of the grant.
4 (2) A description of how the grants were used.
5 (3) The public school units that applied for grants but did not receive one.
6 (4) The extent to which students participating in speech and debate programs
7 funded by the Program experienced measurable improvement in academic
8 performance.
9 SECTION 7.54.(h) Of the funds appropriated to the Department of Public
10 Instruction in this act, the Department shall use the sum of five hundred thousand dollars
11 ($500,000) in recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to establish and administer the
12 Competitive Speech and Debate Team Grant Pilot Program, as established by this section. At the
13 conclusion of the Program, when creating the base budget for the 2029-2031 fiscal biennium, the
14 Director of the Budget shall not include these funds for the 2029-2030 fiscal year.
