16 NORTHEAST REGIONAL SCHOOL OF BIOTECHNOLOGY AND AGRISCIENCE
17 SECTION 7.55.(a) Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by adding a
18 new Article to read:
19 "Article 15A.
20 "Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience.
21 "§ 115C-229.5. Purpose.
22 (a) The purpose of this Article is to establish the Northeast Regional School of
23 Biotechnology and Agriscience as a school of choice that will expand student opportunities for
24 educational success through high quality instructional programming in the northeastern region
25 of the State. The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience may partner with
26 other education partners, including local boards of education, institutions of higher education, or
27 private businesses or organizations, and shall foster, encourage, and promote the development of
28 knowledge and skills in career clusters of critical importance to the region.
29 (b) The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience is a political
30 subdivision of the State and shall operate as a public school unit with a board of directors as the
31 governing body.
32 (c) Except as otherwise provided in this Article and Article 7B of this Chapter, the
33 Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience is exempt from statutes and rules
34 applicable to a local board of education or local school administrative unit.
35 "§ 115C-229.10. Definitions.
36 The following definitions apply in this Part:
37 (1) Regional school. – The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and
38 Agriscience.
39 (2) Regional school board of directors or board of directors. – The governing
40 board of the Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience.
41 (3) Regional school service area. – The counties of Beaufort, Bertie, Camden,
42 Currituck, Dare, Edenton, Edgecombe, Gates, Halifax, Hertford, Hyde,
43 Martin, Northampton, Pasquotank, Perquimans, Pitt, Tyrrell, and Washington.
44 "§ 115C-229.15. Board of directors; appointment; terms of office.
45 (a) The board of directors of the regional school shall consist of the following members:
46 (1) The Superintendent of Public Instruction shall appoint three members who are
47 either a local board of education member or superintendent of a local school
48 administrative unit in a county where at least five percent (5%) of the students
49 enrolled in the regional school reside.
50 (2) The State Board of Education shall appoint five members as representatives
51 of the business community, upon the recommendation of the North Carolina
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 147

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Economic Developers Association, who reside in a county where at least five
2 percent (5%) of the students enrolled in the regional school reside. At least
3 one of the appointees shall be a resident of the county in which the regional
4 school is located.
5 (3) The Parent Advisory Council established by G.S. 115C-229.20 shall appoint
6 one member to the board of directors from among the Council membership.
7 The seat shall be declared vacant if the child of the appointed parent no longer
8 attends the regional school.
9 (4) Any institution of higher education partner may appoint a representative of
10 the institution of higher education to serve as an ex officio member of the
11 board of directors.
12 (b) Members shall serve four-year terms of office. Appointed members of the board of
13 directors shall be selected for their interest in and commitment to the importance of public
14 education to regional economic development and to the purposes of the regional school.
15 (c) Whenever an appointed member of the board of directors ceases to meet the
16 qualifications for appointment or for any reason other than ill health or service in the interest of
17 the State or nation to be present at three successive regular meetings of the board of directors, his
18 or her place as a member of the board of directors shall be deemed vacant. Any member of the
19 board of directors may be removed from office by the appointing authority for misfeasance,
20 malfeasance, or nonfeasance in office. All vacancies shall be filled by the appointing authority
21 for the remainder of the term of office by an individual meeting the qualifications for the vacated
22 seat.
23 "§ 115C-229.20. Parent Advisory Council; purpose; appointments.
24 (a) Purpose. – There shall be a Parent Advisory Council to serve as a resource and provide
25 input to the board of directors as to the operation of the regional school. The board of directors
26 shall consult the Parent Advisory Council when considering changes to the regional school's
27 operations that may significantly impact students attending the regional school.
28 (b) Appointment. – The Superintendent of Public Instruction shall appoint one member
29 from each county where at least five percent (5%) of the students enrolled in the regional school
30 reside to the Parent Advisory Council for a term of four years or until the member's child no
31 longer attends the regional school. Appointees shall be parents or guardians of students attending
32 the regional school and shall, to the extent possible, reflect the demographic composition of the
33 regional school.
34 "§ 115C-229.25. Board of directors; meetings; rules of procedure; officers.
35 (a) The board of directors shall meet at least four times a year and may hold special
36 meetings at any time at the call of the chair or upon petition addressed to the chair by a majority
37 of the members of the board of directors. All meetings of the board of directors shall be subject
38 to the requirements of Article 33C of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes.
39 (b) The board of directors shall elect a chair and a vice-chair from among its members,
40 who shall serve a two-year term.
41 (c) All members of the board of directors shall be voting members except for the chair,
42 who may vote only on matters to break a tie.
43 (d) The board of directors shall determine its own rules of procedure and may delegate
44 to such committees as it may create such of its powers as it deems appropriate.
45 (e) Members of the board of directors shall receive such per diem compensation and
46 necessary travel and subsistence expenses while engaged in the discharge of their official duties
47 as is provided by law for members of State boards and commissions.
48 "§ 115C-229.30. Board of directors; corporate powers.
49 (a) The board of directors of the regional school shall be known and distinguished by the
50 name of "The Northeast Regional School of Biotechnology and Agriscience Board of Directors"
51 and shall continue as a body politic and corporate and by that name shall have perpetual
