17 "§ 115C-229.35. Board of directors; powers and duties.
18 The board of directors shall have the following powers and duties:
19 (1) The board of directors shall establish the regional school's academic program
20 in accordance with the following:
21 a. The board of directors shall establish the standard course of study for
22 the regional school. This course of study shall set forth the subjects to
23 be taught in each grade and the texts and other educational materials
24 on each subject to be used in each grade. The board of directors shall
25 design its programs to meet at least the student performance standards
26 adopted by the State Board of Education and the student performance
27 standards contained in this Chapter.
28 b. The board of directors shall conduct student assessments required by
29 the State Board of Education.
30 c. The board of directors shall provide the opportunity to earn or obtain
31 credit toward degrees from a community college subject to Chapter
32 115D of the General Statutes or a constituent institution of The
33 University of North Carolina.
34 d. The board of directors shall adopt a school calendar consisting of a
35 minimum of 185 days or 1,025 hours of instruction covering at least
36 nine calendar months.
37 e. The board of directors shall ensure that financial literacy instruction is
38 provided as required by the State Board of Education pursuant to
39 G.S. 115C-81.65, including required professional development for
40 teachers of the EPF course.
41 (2) The board of directors shall establish policies and standards for academic
42 performance, attendance, and conduct for students of the regional school. The
43 policies of the board of directors shall comply with Article 27 of this Chapter.
44 (3) Every parent, guardian, or other person in this State having charge or control
45 of a child who is enrolled in the regional school and who is less than 16 years
46 of age shall cause the child to attend school continuously for a period equal to
47 the time that the regional school shall be in session. No person shall
48 encourage, entice, or counsel any child to be unlawfully absent from the
49 regional school. Any person who aids or abets a student's unlawful absence
50 from the regional school shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a Class 1
51 misdemeanor. The principal shall be responsible for implementing such
