1 additional policies concerning compulsory attendance as shall be adopted by
2 the board of directors, including regulations concerning lawful and unlawful
3 absences, permissible excuses for temporary absences, maintenance of
4 attendance records, and attendance counseling.
5 (4) The board of directors shall comply with the reporting requirements
6 established by the State Board of Education in the Uniform Education
7 Reporting System.
8 (5) The board of directors shall require compliance with laws and policies relating
9 to the education of children with disabilities. The school is subject to and shall
10 comply with Article 9 of this Chapter and The Individuals with Disabilities
11 Education Improvements Act, 20 U.S.C. § 1400.
12 (6) The board of directors shall require that the regional school meet the same
13 health and safety standards required of a local school administrative unit.
14 (7) The board of directors shall require the regional school to comply with
15 G.S. 115C-375.2A and shall provide the school with a supply of emergency
16 epinephrine auto-injectors necessary to carry out the provisions of that section.
17 (8) The regional school shall comply with the requirements for public school units
18 in Part 2 of Article 8C of this Chapter.
19 (9) The regional school shall implement the rule addressing student awareness of
20 child abuse and neglect, including sexual abuse, adopted by the State Board
21 of Education under G.S. 115C-12(47).
22 (10) The board of directors shall apply the rules and policies established by the
23 State Board of Education for issuance of driving eligibility certificates.
24 (11) The regional school shall comply with G.S. 115C-407.40 regarding cultural
25 expression at all graduation ceremonies.
26 (12) The regional school shall strive to ensure that one hundred percent (100%)
27 muscadine grape juice is made available to students as a part of the school's
28 nutrition program or through the operation of the school's vending facilities.
29 (13) If the regional school organizes athletic teams for middle or high school
30 students to participate in interscholastic or intramural athletic activities, those
31 teams shall be organized in accordance with G.S. 115C-12(23).
32 (14) The board of directors shall comply with the purchasing and contract statutes
33 and regulations applicable to local school administrative units.
34 (15) The board of directors shall be exempt from Chapter 150B of the General
35 Statutes, except final decisions of the board of directors in a contested case
36 shall be subject to judicial review in accordance with Article 4 of Chapter
37 150B of the General Statutes.
38 (16) The regional school shall ensure that the report card issued for it by the State
39 Board of Education receives wide distribution to the local press or is otherwise
40 provided to the public. A regional school shall ensure that the overall school
41 performance score and grade earned by the regional school for the current and
42 previous four school years is prominently displayed on the school website. If
43 a regional school earned an overall school performance grade of D or F, the
44 regional school shall provide notice of the grade in writing to the parent or
45 guardian of all students enrolled in that school.
46 (17) The board of directors is encouraged to adopt a policy against bullying or
47 harassing behavior, including cyber-bullying, for the regional school that is
48 consistent with the provisions of Article 29C of this Chapter. If the board of
49 directors adopts a policy to prohibit bullying and harassing behavior, the
50 regional school shall, at the beginning of each school year, provide the policy
51 to staff, students, and parents as defined in G.S. 115C-390.1(b)(8).
