10 DIABETES EDUCATION FOR PARENTS
11 SECTION 7.57. G.S. 115C-375.3 reads as rewritten:
12 "§ 115C-375.3. Guidelines to support and assist students with diabetes.
13 (a) Local boards of education and boards of directors of charter schools Governing bodies
14 of public school units shall ensure that the guidelines adopted by the State Board of Education
15 under G.S. 115C-12(31) are implemented in schools in which students with diabetes are enrolled.
16 In particular, the boards shall require the implementation of the procedures set forth in those
17 guidelines for the development and implementation of individual diabetes care plans. The boards
18 also shall make available necessary information and staff development to teachers and school
19 personnel in order to appropriately support and assist students with diabetes in accordance with
20 their individual diabetes care plans.
21 (b) Governing bodies of public school units shall ensure that each school provides parents
22 and legal guardians with information about type 1 and type 2 diabetes at the beginning of every
23 school year. This information shall include all of the following:
24 (1) A description of type 1 and type 2 diabetes.
25 (2) A description of the risk factors and warning signs associated with type 1 and
26 type 2 diabetes.
27 (3) A recommendation that if a student is displaying warning signs associated
28 with diabetes, the parent or guardian of the student consult with the primary
29 care provider of the student to determine if immediate screening for diabetes
30 is appropriate.
31 (4) A description of the screening process for and stages of diabetes.
32 (5) A recommendation that if a student receives a diabetes diagnosis, the parent
33 or guardian of the student consult with the primary care provider of the student
34 to develop an appropriate treatment plan.
35 (6) Notification that the school is required to assist students with diabetes in
36 accordance with the rules adopted by the State Board of Education pursuant
37 to G.S. 115C-12(31)."
