17 A principal's placement on the applicable salary schedule shall be determined
18 according to the average daily membership of the school supervised by the principal, as described
19 in subsection (b) of this section, and the school growth scores, calculated pursuant to
20 G.S. 115C-83.15(c), for each school the principal supervised in at least two of the prior three
21 school years, as described in subsection (c) of this section, regardless of a break in service, and
22 provided the principal supervised each school as a principal for at least a majority of the school
23 year, as follows:
24 (1) A principal shall be paid according to the Exceeded Growth column of the
25 schedule if the school growth scores show the school or schools exceeded
26 expected growth in at least two of the prior three school years.
27 (2) A principal shall be paid according to the Met Growth column of the schedule
28 if any of the following apply:
29 a. The school growth scores show the school or schools met expected
30 growth in at least two of the prior three school years.
31 b. The school growth scores show the school or schools met expected
32 growth in at least one of the prior three school years and exceeded
33 expected growth in one of the prior three school years.
34 c. The principal supervised a school in at least two of the prior three
35 school years that was not eligible to receive a school growth score.
36 (3) A principal shall be paid according to the Base column if any of the following
37 apply:
38 a. The school growth scores show the school or schools did not meet
39 expected growth in at least two of the prior three school years.
40 b. The principal has not supervised any school as a principal for a
41 majority of the school year in at least two of the prior three school
42 years.
