36 ESTABLISH SCHOOL OF CIVIC LIFE AND LEADERSHIP
37 SECTION 8.2.(a) Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
38 Article to read:
39 "Article 31B.
40 "The School of Civic Life and Leadership.
41 "§ 116-258.1. The School of Civic Life and Leadership established.
42 (a) For purposes of this Article, the term "the School" refers to the School of Civic Life
43 and Leadership established pursuant to subsection (b) of this section.
44 (b) The Board of Trustees of the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, in
45 consultation with the Board of Governors of The University of North Carolina, the Provost of
46 the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, and faculty and administration officials at the
47 University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, shall establish the School of Civic Life and
48 Leadership as a separate reporting unit of the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
49 "§ 116-258.2. Scope.
50 The School shall do at least the following:
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 181

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Provide course opportunities for students. Courses may focus on the
2 development of democratic competencies informed by American history, the
3 American political tradition, and the study of the great texts and traditions of
4 Western civilization that form the foundation of the American republic. The
5 purpose of these courses is to foster public discourse and civil engagement
6 necessary to promote democracy and benefit society.
7 (2) Develop programming to address the topics identified in subdivision (1) of
8 this section and provide resources to students, faculty, and the general public,
9 as needed.
10 "§ 116-258.3. Faculty.
11 (a) The Dean of the School shall be appointed by the Chancellor of the University of
12 North Carolina at Chapel Hill, with the consent of the Board of Trustees of the University of
13 North Carolina at Chapel Hill. Neither the Chancellor nor the Board of Trustees shall delegate
14 this responsibility to another party.
15 (b) All faculty hired by or appointed to the School shall be subject to the approval of the
16 Dean of the School.
17 (c) Faculty members may hold joint or courtesy appointments with other reporting units
18 of the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. All joint and courtesy appointments shall be
19 made at the discretion of the Dean of the School.
20 "§ 116-258.4. Report.
21 No later than November 15 of each year, the Board of Trustees of the University of North
22 Carolina at Chapel Hill shall report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee and
23 the Fiscal Research Division on the School, including at least the following information:
24 (1) Courses and other programming provided by the School.
25 (2) Faculty hired by the School, including the number of faculty members hired
26 from outside of the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
27 (3) Uses of funds appropriated to the School pursuant to this section.
28 (4) Any other matter the Board deems relevant to the progress of establishing the
29 School."
30 SECTION 8.2.(b) For the 2025-2026 academic year, the following shall occur:
31 (1) The School of Civic Life and Leadership (the School) shall employ at least 20
32 faculty members hired from outside the University of North Carolina at
33 Chapel Hill. These faculty members shall be hired with permanent tenure or
34 be eligible to receive permanent tenure in accordance with policies adopted
35 by The Board of Governors of The University of North Carolina and the
36 University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
37 (2) The School shall not employ any additional faculty by joint or courtesy
38 appointment with other reporting units of the University of North Carolina at
39 Chapel Hill unless the school has employed at least 20 faculty members hired
40 from outside the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in accordance
41 with this subsection.
42 SECTION 8.2.(c) Notwithstanding G.S. 116-30.2, the recurring funds allocated to
43 the School of Civic Life and Leadership (the School) by this section beginning in the 2025-2026
44 fiscal year shall be used only to support the School and shall not be redirected for any other
45 purpose. In addition, these funds shall be used to supplement and not supplant any funds the
46 School would otherwise receive, including funds received by the School based on enrollment.
