5 INSTITUTIONAL PERFORMANCE ACCOUNTABILITY AND FUNDING
6 SECTION 8.20. Part 2A of Article 1 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is
7 amended by adding the following new section to read:
8 "§ 116-30.10. Institutional performance accountability.
9 (a) Implementation of Accountability Measures and Performance Standards. – To the
10 extent funds are available to the Board of Governors pursuant to the provisions of this Chapter
11 or otherwise made available for this purpose, the Board of Governors may adopt and implement
12 a system of accountability measures and performance standards to be used to allocate those funds
13 to constituent institutions of The University of North Carolina.
14 (b) Recognition of Successful Institutional Performance. – The Board may allocate
15 available funds among constituent institutions based on an evaluation of the performance of each
16 institution conducted in accordance with the system of accountability measures and performance
17 standards adopted pursuant to subsection (a) of this section. The evaluation shall include at least
18 the following components:
19 (1) Performance change, based on the rate of student success at a constituent
20 institution as compared to the baseline or goal rate of student success for that
21 constituent institution.
22 (2) Institutional impact, based on the number of students at a constituent
23 institution who graduate with a degree.
24 (c) Institutional Support. – In addition to any funds allocated pursuant to subsection (b)
25 of this section, the Board of Governors may allocate available funds to specific constituent
26 institutions that require targeted support to increase performance or adapt to significant
27 enrollment changes. Funds allocated to an institution pursuant to this subsection may be used to
28 support strategies at the constituent institution to improve institutional performance."
29
