14 COLLABORATORY OLR MATH INITIATIVE
15 SECTION 8.25.(a) The Office of Learning Research (OLR), as established by this
16 act, shall develop a series of pilot initiatives using various mathematics support programs for all
17 grade levels. OLR shall then compare results gathered from the initiatives, including existing
18 high-intensity tutoring programs operating in the State, to evaluate the efficacy of the various
19 initiatives and programs. OLR shall use at least the following programs in the initiatives
20 developed pursuant to this section:
21 (1) Zearn Math, by Zearn.
22 (2) i-Ready Math, by Curriculum Associates, LLC.
23 SECTION 8.25.(a1) OLR shall also consider for inclusion in initiatives developed
24 pursuant to subsection (a) of this section the following math programs:
25 (1) ST Math, by the International MIND Education Institute, Inc.
26 (2) Patterns, by Carnegie Learning, Inc.
27 SECTION 8.25.(b) OLR shall develop guidelines for initiatives developed pursuant
28 to this section. Guidelines shall include at least the following:
29 (1) Acceptable uses for any funds provided to public school units from funds
30 appropriated to OLR for the purposes of this section.
31 (2) Application and approval processes for public school units interested in
32 participating in an initiative.
33 (3) Reporting requirements for public school units participating in each initiative
34 so that OLR will have necessary data to evaluate the efficacy of each initiative.
35 SECTION 8.25.(c) OLR may conduct as many different initiatives as OLR deems
36 feasible with funds available for this purpose. OLR shall attempt to control for varying
37 demographics of public school units when evaluating data collected pursuant to this section.
38 SECTION 8.25.(d) OLR shall develop procedures for enabling public school units
39 participating in an initiative to have access to the programs referenced in subsection (b) of this
40 section. Procedures may include OLR contracting with an entity for access to a program,
41 providing grant funds to participating public school units, or other methods of procuring the
42 programs.
43 SECTION 8.25.(e) OLR shall report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight
44 Committee on the efficacy of each initiative developed pursuant to this section by October 15,
45 2026, and each year thereafter that funds are received for this purpose. The report shall include
46 evaluations of which programs are most effective at improving mathematics outcomes and
47 recommendations on programs to continue use in the public schools of the State.
48 SECTION 8.25.(f) Notwithstanding Article 31A of Chapter 116 of the General
49 Statutes, funds appropriated for the purposes of this section shall only be used to develop and
50 implement the initiatives developed pursuant to this section.
