21 NURSING FELLOWS PILOT PROGRAM AT WINSTON-SALEM STATE
22 UNIVERSITY
23 SECTION 8A.10.(a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
24 (1) Academic term. – A semester or summer session.
25 (2) Authority. – The State Education Assistance Authority.
26 (3) Dean. – The Dean of the School of Health Sciences at WSSU.
27 (4) Eligible nurse. – A nurse who meets all of the following criteria:
28 a. Enrolled at WSSU beginning in the 2026-2027 or 2027-2028
29 academic year.
30 b. Received a forgivable loan under the Program.
31 c. Graduated within 10 years from at least one of the following at WSSU,
32 excluding any authorized deferment for extenuating circumstances:
33 1. A Bachelor of Science in Nursing program.
34 2. A Master of Science in Nursing Education program.
35 d. Is licensed as a registered nurse in this State.
36 (5) Forgivable loan. – A forgivable loan made under the Program.
37 (6) Program. – The Nursing Fellows Pilot Program.
38 (7) Qualifying nurse. – An eligible nurse who meets all of the following criteria:
39 a. Holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing from WSSU.
40 b. Is employed as a nurse in this State.
41 (8) Qualifying nurse instructor. – An eligible nurse who meets all of the following
42 criteria:
43 a. Holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing from WSSU and a
44 Master of Science degree in Nursing Education from WSSU.
45 b. Is employed as an instructor in a qualifying nursing program.
46 (9) Qualifying nursing program. – A nursing program at one of the following that
47 prepares students to earn a degree in nursing and become a licensed practical
48 nurse as defined in Article 9A of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes:
49 a. A community college.
50 b. A university or private postsecondary institution.
51 (10) Trust Fund. – The Nursing Fellows Program Trust Fund.
Page 212 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (11) University or private postsecondary institution. – Either of the following:
2 a. A postsecondary constituent institution of The University of North
3 Carolina as defined in G.S. 116-2(4).
4 b. An eligible private postsecondary educational institution as defined in
5 G.S. 116-280(3).
6 (12) WSSU. – Winston-Salem State University.
7 SECTION 8A.10.(b) Program. – There is established the Nursing Fellows Pilot
8 Program. The purpose of the Program is to recruit, prepare, and support eligible nursing students
9 enrolling at WSSU beginning in the 2026-2027 and 2027-2028 academic years for preparation
10 as highly effective nurses and instructors in qualifying nursing programs. The Program shall be
11 used to provide forgivable loans to nursing students who are (i) enrolled in degree programs at
12 WSSU to receive a Bachelor of Science in Nursing or a Master of Science in Nursing Education
13 and (ii) interested in preparing to become nurses in the State or instructors in qualifying nursing
14 programs.
15 SECTION 8A.10.(c) Program Administration; Dean. – The Authority shall
16 administer the Program in cooperation with the Dean. The Dean shall determine forgivable loan
17 recipient selection criteria and selection procedures and shall select the recipients to receive
18 forgivable loans under the Program in accordance with the requirements of this section. The Dean
19 shall appoint any needed staff of the Program and shall be responsible for recruitment and
20 coordination of the Program, including proactive, aggressive, and strategic recruitment of
21 potential recipients. Recruitment activities shall include (i) targeting regions of the State with the
22 greatest need for nurses and nursing instructors in qualifying nursing programs, (ii) actively
23 engaging with registered nurses, business leaders, experts in human resources, elected officials,
24 and other community leaders throughout the State, and (iii) attracting candidates to the Program.
25 WSSU shall provide office space and clerical support staff, as necessary, to the Dean for the
26 Program.
27 SECTION 8A.10.(d) Trust Fund. – There is established the Nursing Fellows
28 Program Trust Fund to be administered by the Authority, in conjunction with the Dean. All funds
29 (i) appropriated to, or otherwise received by, the Program for forgivable loans and other Program
30 purposes, (ii) received as repayment of forgivable loans, and (iii) earned as interest on these funds
31 shall be placed in the Trust Fund. The purpose of the Trust Fund is to provide financial assistance
32 to qualified students to fill needed positions for nurses in the State and instructors in qualifying
33 nursing programs through completion of a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing or both a
34 Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing and a Master of Science degree in Nursing Education.
35 SECTION 8A.10.(e) Uses of Monies in the Trust Fund. – The monies in the Trust
36 Fund may be used only for forgivable loans granted under the Program, administrative costs
37 associated with the Program, including recruitment and recovery of funds advanced under the
38 Program, mentoring and coaching support to forgivable loan recipients, and extracurricular
39 enhancement activities of the Program in accordance with the following:
40 (1) The Authority shall transfer six percent (6%) of the available funds from the
41 Trust Fund to WSSU at the beginning of each fiscal year for the following
42 purposes:
43 a. The Program's administrative costs.
44 b. Extracurricular enhancement activities of the Program.
45 c. Mentoring and coaching support to forgivable loan recipients.
46 (2) The Authority may use up to four percent (4%) of the funds appropriated to
47 the Trust Fund each fiscal year for administrative costs associated with the
48 Program.
49 SECTION 8A.10.(f) Student Selection Criteria for Forgivable Loans. – The Dean,
50 in consultation with the Associate Dean of Nursing at WSSU, shall adopt stringent standards for
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 213

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 awarding forgivable loans based on multiple measures to ensure that only the strongest applicants
2 receive them, including the following:
3 (1) Grade point averages.
4 (2) Performance on relevant assessments.
5 (3) Experience, accomplishments, and other criteria demonstrating qualities
6 positively correlated with highly effective nurses and instructors in qualifying
7 nursing programs, including excellent verbal and communication skills.
8 (4) Demonstrated commitment to serve in North Carolina.
9 SECTION 8A.10.(g) Awards of Forgivable Loans. – The Program shall provide
10 forgivable loans to selected students who are initially enrolled in a Bachelor of Science in
11 Nursing degree program at WSSU. Loan payments shall be provided each year for completion
12 of the Bachelor of Science in Nursing program and, if a loan recipient seeks to become a
13 qualifying nurse instructor, for a Master of Science in Nursing Education program. The student
14 shall be eligible to receive loan payments for the Master of Science in Nursing Education
15 program as long as the student enrolls within two years of graduation from the Bachelor of
16 Science in Nursing program. Forgivable loans may be used for tuition, fees, the cost of books,
17 and expenses related to completing a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing and a Master of
18 Science degree in Nursing Education. Forgivable loans shall be awarded per academic term in
19 amounts of up to five thousand dollars ($5,000) per semester or two thousand five hundred dollars
20 ($2,500) per summer session, as follows:
21 (1) For students pursuing careers as qualifying nurses, for up to five semesters.
22 (2) For persons pursuing careers as qualifying nurse instructors, for up to nine
23 semesters.
24 SECTION 8A.10.(h) Administration of Forgivable Loan Awards. – Upon the
25 naming of recipients of the forgivable loans by the Dean, the Dean shall transfer to the Authority
26 its decisions. The Authority, in coordination with the Dean, shall perform all of the administrative
27 functions necessary to implement this section, which functions shall include rulemaking,
28 disseminating information, acting as a liaison with participating institutions of higher education,
29 implementing forgivable loan agreements, loan monitoring, loan canceling through service and
30 collection, determining the acceptability of service repayment agreements, enforcing the
31 agreements, and all other functions necessary for the execution, payment, and enforcement of
32 promissory notes required under this section.
33 SECTION 8A.10.(i) Annual Report. – The Dean, in coordination with the Authority,
34 shall report no later than January 1, 2027, and annually thereafter while forgivable loans are being
35 serviced under the Program, to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee regarding
36 the following:
37 (1) Forgivable loans awarded from the Trust Fund, including the following:
38 a. Demographic information regarding recipients.
39 b. Number of recipients by institution of higher education.
40 (2) Placement and repayment rates, including the following:
41 a. Number of graduates who have been employed as qualifying nurses in
42 the State and qualifying nurse instructors in qualifying nursing
43 programs within two years of graduation.
44 b. Number of graduates who have elected to do loan repayment and their
45 years of service, if any, prior to beginning loan repayment.
46 c. Graduation rates of associate degree students taught by instructors in
47 qualifying nursing programs who are recipients of loans under the
48 Program.
49 (3) Mentoring and coaching support, including the number of forgivable loan
50 recipients who received mentoring and coaching support.
