6 SECTION 8A.10.(j) Terms of Forgivable Loans. – All forgivable loans shall be
7 evidenced by notes made payable to the Authority that bear interest at a rate not to exceed ten
8 percent (10%) per year as set by the Authority and beginning on the first day of September after
9 completion of the applicable degree program or 90 days after graduation, whichever is later. If a
10 forgivable loan is terminated, the note shall be made payable to the Authority 90 days after
11 termination of the forgivable loan. The forgivable loan may be terminated upon the recipient's
12 withdrawal from the Program or by the recipient's failure to meet the standards set by the Dean.
13 SECTION 8A.10.(k) Forgiveness. – For every year a qualifying nurse remains a
14 qualifying nurse or a qualifying nurse instructor remains a qualifying nurse instructor, the
15 Authority shall forgive one-third of the total loan amount received over the course of enrollment
16 in the applicable degree program and any interest accrued on that amount. The Authority shall
17 also forgive the loan if it finds that it is impossible for the recipient to work for up to three years,
18 within 10 years after completion of the Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree program for
19 persons pursuing forgiveness as qualifying nurses or of the Master of Science in Nursing
20 Education degree program for persons pursuing forgiveness as qualifying nurse instructors,
21 because of the death or permanent disability of the recipient. If the recipient repays the forgivable
22 loan by cash payments, all indebtedness shall be repaid within 10 years after completion of the
23 latest applicable degree program supported by the forgivable loan. If the recipient completes the
24 applicable degree program, payment of principal and interest shall begin no later than the first
25 day of September after the completion of the program. Should a recipient present extenuating
26 circumstances, the Authority may extend the period to repay the loan in cash to no more than a
27 total of 12 years.
28 SECTION 8A.10.(l) Notwithstanding G.S. 116-209.45(h), beginning in the
29 2026-2027 fiscal year, to the extent funds remain available in the Forgivable Education Loans
30 for Service Fund at the end of each fiscal year, the Authority may use those funds to administer
31 the Nursing Fellows Pilot Program in accordance with this section.
32 SECTION 8A.10.(m) The Dean of the School of Health Sciences at Winston-Salem
33 State University shall establish initial selection criteria for recipients no later than November 15,
34 2025, and shall make available applications to prospective students no later than December 31,
35 2025.
36 SECTION 8A.10.(n) The Dean of the School of Health Sciences at Winston-Salem
37 State University shall select recipients and award the initial forgivable loans for the 2026-2027
38 academic year no later than April 1, 2026.
39 SECTION 8A.10.(o) This section applies beginning with applications for enrollment
