5 "§ 131A-32. The Rural Health Care Stabilization Sustainability Fund.
6 The Rural Health Care Stabilization Sustainability Fund is created as a nonreverting special
7 fund in the Office of State Budget and Management. The Fund shall operate as a revolving fund
8 consisting of funds appropriated to, or otherwise received by, the Rural Health Care Stabilization
9 Sustainability Program and all funds received as repayment of the principal of or interest on a
10 loan made from the Fund. The State Treasurer is the custodian of the Fund and shall invest its
11 assets in accordance with G.S. 147-69.2 and G.S. 147-69.3. Moneys in the Fund shall only be
12 used for loans made pursuant to this Article.
