18 "§ 143B-139.4E. Authority to contract with nonprofit corporation to administer Rural
19 Health Care Sustainability Program.
20 (a) Authority to Contract; Requirements and Limitations. – The Department of Health
21 and Human Services, Division of Central Management and Support, Office of Rural Health
22 (Office of Rural Health), is authorized to contract with a North Carolina 501(c)(6) nonprofit
23 corporation to serve as the Program Administrator for the Rural Health Care Sustainability
24 Program authorized by Article 2 of Chapter 131A of the General Statutes and, in that capacity,
25 perform the duties and responsibilities prescribed by G.S. 131A-31(b). This authorization is
26 subject to the following requirements and limitations:
27 (1) At least 45 days prior to entering into or amending in a nontechnical manner
28 a contract authorized by this section, the Office of Rural Health shall submit
29 the contract or amendment, along with a detailed explanation of the contract
30 or amendment, to the chairs of both the Senate Committee on
31 Appropriations/Base Budget and the House of Representatives Committee on
32 Appropriations, the chairs of the Senate Appropriations Committee on Health
33 and Human Services, the chairs of the House Appropriations Committee on
34 Health and Human Services, and the Fiscal Research Division.
35 (2) Prior to entering into a contract authorized by this section, the nonprofit
36 corporation shall establish a Loan Committee that it shall maintain for the
37 duration of the contract with the following governance provisions:
38 a. The Loan Committee shall be composed of seven voting members as
39 follows: two members appointed by the General Assembly upon
40 recommendation of the Speaker of the House of Representatives; two
41 members appointed by the General Assembly upon recommendation
42 of the President Pro Tempore of the Senate; and the remaining three
43 members appointed as provided in the bylaws of the nonprofit
44 corporation. Appointing authorities shall select appointees with
45 expertise and experience in a health care discipline that includes rural
46 health care planning, management, and operations. No State employee
47 or elected official may serve on the Loan Committee.
48 b. The Loan Committee shall meet at least quarterly at the call of its chair.
49 c. Members of the Loan Committee shall not be compensated for their
50 services and no State funds shall be used to provide per diems or
51 allowances to any member of the Loan Committee.
