26 never been served in other early education programs such as child care, public
27 or private preschool, Head Start, Early Head Start, or early intervention
28 programs.
29 (3) The expected NC Pre-K expenditures for the programs and the source of the
30 local contributions.
31 (4) The results of an annual evaluation of the NC Pre-K program.
32 SECTION 9D.1.(g) Audits. – The administration of the NC Pre-K program by local
33 partnerships shall be subject to the financial and compliance audits authorized under
