3 SECTION 9D.8. Article 7 of Chapter 110 of the General Statutes is amended by
4 adding a new section to read:
5 "§ 110-106.3. Exemption for certain Department of Defense family child care homes from
6 child care licensure requirements.
7 (a) The provisions of this Article shall not apply to a family child care home operating in
8 this State and located outside of the boundaries of a military installation if the family child care
9 home has a certificate issued by the United States Department of Defense (DOD) or the United
10 States Coast Guard to provide child care and has completed background screening by the DOD
11 pursuant to 34 U.S.C. § 20351 and 32 C.F.R. Part 86 and received a favorable suitability and
12 fitness determination. This exemption applies to DOD family child care home operators
13 providing child care to children eligible for care under the DOD Instruction 6060.02.
14 (b) A family child care home seeking to operate pursuant to this section shall register
15 with the Department. The individual at each military installation who provides oversight of
16 family child care homes shall be responsible for registering the family child care home operating
17 under this section with the Department. The Department shall establish and maintain a registry
18 in accordance with this section and the registry shall be used for the following limited purposes:
19 (1) Ensuring the DOD family child care home is fully compliant with all DOD
20 requirements to operate the family child care home.
21 (2) Certifying that the following State safety provisions are met for the dwelling
22 unit in which the DOD family child care home is located:
23 a. Rooms and areas within a family child care home where occupants
24 receive care are located on the same level of exit discharge.
25 b. Rooms and areas within a family child care home where occupants
26 receive care are located on the same level with, and within a maximum
27 of 40 feet travel distance to, at least one 2A:10B:C fire extinguisher.
28 c. The family child care home has and maintains a Fire Safety,
29 Evacuation, and Lockdown Plan compliant with Section 404 of the
30 North Carolina Fire Code.
31 d. The family child care home has carbon monoxide alarm and detection
32 systems compliant with Section R315 of the North Carolina
33 Residential Code.
34 e. The family child care home has smoke alarms compliant with Section
35 51 R314 of the North Carolina Residential Code.
36 (3) Receiving confirmation from the person operating the DOD family child care
37 home that the family child care home is within the same dwelling unit
38 occupied by the operator.
39 (4) Confirming inquiries regarding a DOD family child care home are directed to
40 the appropriate regulatory authority having oversight of family child care
41 homes for the respective military installation.
42 (c) A DOD family child care home that meets the requirements of this section shall be
43 exempt from all other requirements of this Article and shall not be subject to licensure."
