19 "§ 108A-147.5. Presumptive service cost component.
20 (a) For every State fiscal quarter prior to the fiscal quarter in which G.S. 108A-54.3A(24)
21 becomes effective, the presumptive service cost component is zero.
22 (b) For the State fiscal quarter in which G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) becomes effective, the
23 presumptive service cost component is the product of forty-eight million seven hundred fifty
24 thousand dollars ($48,750,000) multiplied by the number of months in that State fiscal quarter in
25 which G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) is effective during any part of the month.
26 (c) For the first State fiscal quarter after the State fiscal quarter in which
27 G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) becomes effective, the presumptive service cost component is one hundred
28 forty-six million two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($146,250,000).
29 (d) For the second State fiscal quarter after the State fiscal quarter in which
30 G.S. 108A-54.3A(24) becomes effective, and for each State fiscal quarter thereafter, the
31 presumptive service cost component is an amount of money that is the greatest of the following:
32 (1) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount.
33 (2) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount increased by
34 a percentage that is the sum of each monthly percentage change in the
35 Consumer Price Index: Medical Care for the most recent three months
36 available on the first day of the current quarter.
37 (3) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount increased by
38 the percentage change in the weighted average of the base capitation rates for
39 standard benefit plans for all rating groups associated with newly eligible
40 individuals compared to the prior quarter. The weight for each rating group
41 shall be calculated using member months documented in the Medicaid
42 managed care capitation rate certification for standard benefit plans.
43 (4) The prior quarter's presumptive service cost component amount increased by
44 the percentage change in the weighted average of the base capitation rates for
45 BH IDD tailored plans for all rating groups associated with newly eligible
46 individuals compared to the prior quarter. The weight for each rating group
47 shall be calculated using member months documented in the Medicaid
48 managed care capitation rate certification for BH IDD tailored plans.
49 (5) The amount produced from multiplying 1.15 by the highest amount produced
50 when calculating, for each quarter that is at least two and not more than five
51 quarters prior to the current quarter, the actual nonfederal expenditures for the
