31 SECTION 9F.1.(a) G.S. 131E-147.5, as enacted by Section 3.2(c) of S.L. 2023-7,
32 reads as rewritten:
33 "§ 131E-147.5. Charity care requirement for qualified urban ambulatory surgical
34 facilities; annual report.
35 (a) The percentage of each qualified urban ambulatory surgical facility's total earned
36 revenue that is attributed to self-pay and Medicaid revenue shall be equivalent to at least four
37 percent (4%), calculated as follows: the Medicare allowable amount for self-pay and Medicaid
38 surgical cases minus all revenue earned from self-pay and Medicaid cases, divided by the total
39 earned revenues for all surgical cases, divided by the total earned revenues for all surgical cases
40 performed in the facility for procedures for which there is a Medicare allowable fee.
41 (b) Each qualified urban ambulatory surgical facility shall annually report to the
42 Department in the manner prescribed by the Department the percentage of the facility's earned
43 revenue that is attributed to self-pay and Medicaid revenue, as calculated in accordance with
44 subsection (a) of this section.
45 (c) Qualified ambulatory surgical facilities in counties with a population greater than
46 125,000 that were licensed prior to November 21, 2025, are exempt from these requirements."
