16 (4) Data on long-term benefits associated with IFPS. This data shall be obtained
17 by tracking families through the intervention process.
18 (5) The number of families remaining intact and the associated interventions
19 while in IFPS and 12 months thereafter.
20 (6) The number and percentage, by race, of children who received IFPS compared
21 to the ratio of their distribution in the general population involved with Child
22 Protective Services.
