11 CHANGES
12 SECTION 14.1A.(a) G.S. 143B-88 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 143B-88. North Carolina Arts Council – members; selection; quorum; compensation.
14 (a) The North Carolina Arts Council shall consist of 24 members appointed by the
15 Governor. The initial members of the Council shall be the appointed members of the present Arts
16 Council who shall serve for a period equal to the remainder of their current terms on the Arts
17 Council, eight of whose terms expire June 30, 1973, eight of whose terms expire June 30, 1974,
18 and eight of whose terms expire June 30, 1975. At the end of the respective terms of office of the
19 initial members, the appointments of their successors shall be for terms of three years and until
20 their successors are appointed and qualify. Any appointment to fill a vacancy on the Council
21 created by the resignation, dismissal, death, or disability of a member shall be for the balance of
22 the unexpired term.nine members.
23 The Governor shall have the power to remove any member of the Council from office in
24 accordance with the provisions of G.S. 143B-16 of the Executive Organization Act of 1973.
25 The Governor shall designate a member of the Council as chairman to serve at his pleasure.
26 (b) The members of the North Carolina Arts Council shall be appointed as follows:
27 (1) The Governor shall appoint three members for three-year terms.
28 (2) The General Assembly shall appoint six members for three-year terms, three
29 upon the recommendation of the Speaker of the House of Representatives and
30 three upon the recommendation of the President Pro Tempore of the Senate,
31 in accordance with G.S. 120‑121.
32 (c) As the terms of office of the members of the Council appointed by the Governor
33 expire, their successors shall be appointed for terms of three years each. As the terms of office
34 of the members of the Council appointed by the General Assembly expire, their successors shall
35 be appointed for terms of three years each. All members shall serve at the pleasure of the
36 appointing authority, and they may be removed by the appointing authority at any time.
37 In the event that a Council member is removed, the member appointed to replace the removed
38 member shall serve only for the unexpired term of the removed member. Any appointment to fill
39 a vacancy on the Council created by the resignation, dismissal, death, or disability of a member
40 shall be for the balance of the unexpired term.
41 (d) The Council shall elect from its appointive members a chair and other officers as it
42 may choose, for such terms as it may designate in its rules.
43 (e) Members of the Council shall receive per diem and necessary travel and subsistence
44 expenses in accordance with the provisions of G.S. 138-5. A majority of the Council shall
45 constitute a quorum for the transaction of business. All clerical and other services required by
46 the Council shall be supplied by the Secretary of Natural and Cultural Resources."
47 SECTION 14.1A.(b) The present members of the North Carolina Arts Council
