51 "§ 58-31B-45. Claims submission and adjudication.
Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition Page 401

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (a) A State department, agency, or institution required under this Part to make
2 contributions to the Self-insurance Fund shall submit a claim to the Self-insurance Fund when
3 that department, agency, or institution experiences loss or damage to State property as a result of
4 a peril. The Self-insurance Fund shall process all claims submitted under this Part. The
5 Self-insurance Fund shall pay claims associated with loss or damage in an amount not exceeding
6 the amount that it would cost to repair or replace the property with material of like kind and
7 quality within a reasonable time after the loss or damage.
8 (b) The amount to be paid for a claim under this section is determined by the Office of
9 State Fire Marshal and the official designated by the State department, agency, or institution
10 controlling the State property for which the claim was submitted. If an agreement as to the extent
11 of the loss or damage related to that claim cannot be reached between these two parties, then the
12 amount of the loss or damage shall be determined by three appraisers and no claim amount in
13 dispute shall be paid until the completion of that determination. The three appraisers shall be
14 disinterested persons who are qualified from experience to appraise and value property and shall
15 be selected as follows:
16 (1) The State Fire Marshal shall select one appraiser.
17 (2) The official designated by the State department, agency, or institution
18 controlling the property for which the claim was submitted shall select one
19 appraiser.
20 (3) The two appraisers selected by the State Fire Marshal and the designated
21 official shall select a third appraiser. If the appraisers selected by the State Fire
22 Marshal and the designated office fail to agree upon a third appraiser within
23 15 days of their selection, then, on request of the State Fire Marshal or the
24 designated official, a third appraiser shall be selected by the Secretary of the
25 Department of Administration.
26 (c) The appraisers selected and required under this section shall file their written report
27 within 90 days of the selection of all three required appraisers detailing the loss or damage with
28 the Office of State Fire Marshal and with the State department, agency, or institution that
29 submitted the claim.
30 (d) The costs of any appraisal required under this section shall be paid by, and considered
31 an administrative expense of, the Self-insurance Fund.
32 (e) Upon the determination of the loss or damage to the State property made by the
33 appraisers selected and required under this section, the Self-insurance Fund shall pay the claim
34 in full to the applicable State department, agency, or institution.
35 (f) Notwithstanding G.S. 58-2-75 or any other provision of this Chapter to the contrary,
36 the determination of the loss or damage to State property by the appraisers under this section is
37 not appealable and not a contested case under Article 3 of Chapter 150B of the General Statutes."
