9 "§ 55D-19. Paper filing fee.
10 The Office of the Secretary of State may collect a fee of up to ten dollars ($10.00) each time
11 a document is submitted for filing in typewritten or printed form when that same document could
12 be accepted for filing in electronic form. Funds collected under this section shall be deposited in
13 a new budget fund as created by the Office of State Budget and Management within Budget Code
14 23200 and shall only be used for the following purposes: (i) to support activities that will reduce
15 the processing or response time for services provided by the Office, (ii) to improve or streamline
16 the online filing system maintained by the Office, or (iii) to cover costs directly associated with
17 the handling of mail by the Office."
