31 "§ 147-69.2E. Investments in digital assets.
32 (a) The following definitions apply in this section:
33 (1) Designated funds. – Any of the funds described in G.S. 147-69.1(b) and
34 G.S. 147-69.2(a).
35 (2) Digital asset. – A virtual currency, cryptocurrency, native electronic asset,
36 stablecoin, nonfungible token, or any other asset that is only digital and that
37 confers economic, proprietary, or access rights or powers.
38 (3) Private key. – A unique element of cryptographic data used for signing
39 transactions on a blockchain that is known to the owner of the unique element.
40 (4) Secure custody solution. – A technological product or a blended product and
41 service that employs advanced security measures to safeguard private keys
42 and prevent unauthorized access.
43 (b) The Investment Authority may invest the cash of the designated funds in digital assets
44 only after approval by the Board of Directors. The approval shall be based on an independent
45 assessment by a third-party consultant that all of the following requirements for proposed
46 investments have been met:
47 (1) The digital assets are maintained with a secure custody solution.
48 (2) The potential investment is appropriate for the designated fund's
49 circumstances from a total portfolio perspective.
Page 442 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (3) The control environment meets institutional investment industry requirements
2 for independent risk and compliance oversight, operational robustness, and
3 regulatory compliance.
4 (c) An investment in digital assets from any of the designated funds shall not exceed, in
5 the aggregate, five percent (5%) of the balance of the designated fund.
