37 SECTION 38.3.(j) In cooperation with the State Treasurer, the State Bureau of
38 Investigation, local law enforcement agencies, and other statewide law enforcement agencies,
39 shall study the feasibility of establishing the North Carolina Digital Asset Reserve (Reserve),
40 with the purpose of retaining digital assets seized and forfeited to the State. The study shall
41 include at least the following:
42 (1) The State agency or department best suited to administer the Reserve.
43 (2) The best method to hold assets in the Reserve.
44 (3) The process for placing seized or forfeited assets in the Reserve.
45 (4) The best method to time sales from the Reserve to maximize revenue to the
46 Civil Penalty and Forfeiture Fund and benefit local boards of education.
47 (5) Any other issues the stakeholders deem necessary.
48 The State Bureau of Investigation shall report the results of this study, including
49 proposed legislation to create, implement, and administer the Reserve, to the Joint Legislative
50 Oversight Committee on General Government no later than March 1, 2026.
