10 (c) The System shall be considered an authorized representative of the Department of
11 Public Instruction, The University of North Carolina, and the North Carolina System of
12 Community Colleges under applicable federal and State statutes for purposes of accessing and
13 compiling student record data for research purposes.
14 (d) The System shall perform the following functions and duties:
15 (1) Serve as a data broker for the System, including data maintained by the
16 following:
17 a. The Department of Public Instruction.
18 b. Local boards of education, local school administrative units, public
19 schools, and charter schools.
20 c. The University of North Carolina and its constituent institutions.
21 d. The Community Colleges System Office and local community
22 colleges.
23 e. The North Carolina Independent College and Universities, Inc., and
24 private colleges or universities.
25 f. Nonpublic schools serving elementary and secondary students.
26 g. The Department of Commerce, Division of Employment
27 Security.Commerce.
28 h. The Department of Revenue.
29 i. The Department of Health and Human Services.
30 j. The Department of Labor.
31 (2) Ensure routine and ongoing compliance with FERPA, IDEA, HIPAA, CJIS,
32 the Internal Revenue Code, and other relevant privacy laws and policies,
33 including the following:
34 a. The required use of de-identified data in data research and reporting.
35 b. The required disposition of information that is no longer needed.
36 c. Providing data security, including the capacity for audit trails.
37 d. Providing for performance of regular audits for compliance with data
38 privacy and security standards.
39 e. Implementing guidelines and policies that prevent the reporting of
40 other potentially identifying data.
41 (3) Facilitate information and data requests for State and federal education
42 reporting with existing State agencies as appropriate.
43 (4) Facilitate approved public information requests.
44 (5) Develop a process for obtaining information and data requested by the General
45 Assembly and Governor of current de-identified data and research.
46 (e) Use of data accessible through the System shall be regulated in the following ways:
47 (1) Direct access to data shall be restricted to authorized staff of the System.
48 (2) Only de-identified data shall be used in the analysis, research, and reporting
49 conducted by the System.
Page 462 Senate Bill 257-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (3) The System and recipients of data in fulfillment of approved data requests
2 shall only use aggregate aggregated data in the release of data in reports and
3 in response to data requests.public reports.
4 (4) Data that may be identifiable based on the size or uniqueness of the population
5 under consideration shall not be reported in any form by the System.
6 (5) The System shall not release information that may not be disclosed under
7 FERPA, IDEA, HIPAA, CJIS, the Internal Revenue Code, and other relevant
8 privacy laws and policies.
9 (6) Individual or personally identifiable data accessed through the System shall
10 not be a public record under G.S. 132-1.
11 (f) The System may receive funding from the following sources:
12 (1) State appropriations.
13 (2) Grants or other assistance from local school administrative units, public
14 schools, community colleges, constituent institutions of The University of
15 North Carolina, or private colleges and universities.
16 (3) Federal grants.
17 (4) Any other grants or contributions from public or private entities received by
18 the System.
19 (g) Ownership of all data collected and maintained by the System remains with the
20 contributors to the System. Management and disclosure of data by the System does not change
21 ownership of the data.
22 "§ 116E-6. Data sharing.
23 (a) Local school administrative units, Public schools, charter schools, community
