19 LABOR MARKET ADJUSTMENT RESERVE
20 SECTION 41.2A.(a) Of the Labor Market Adjustment Salary Reserve funds
21 appropriated in this act, agencies shall award salary adjustments to identified employees pursuant
22 to the following requirements:
23 (1) Any increase provided to an employee shall not exceed the greater of fifteen
24 thousand dollars ($15,000) or fifteen percent (15%) of their current base
25 salary.
26 (2) Any increase provided to an employee may not result in the employee's salary
27 exceeding the maximum salary of the salary range associated with the
28 position.
29 (3) No more than twenty-five percent (25%) of the agency's permanent employees
30 may receive a salary increase from the funds appropriated for this purpose.
31 (4) Funds may not be awarded to employees in positions with salaries set in law
32 or paid based on an experience-based salary schedule that is eligible to receive
33 funding from the Pay Plan Reserve.
34 (5) Funds must be used to increase salaries paid to employees and shall not be
35 used to supplant other funding sources or for any other purpose.
36 SECTION 41.2A.(b) The Director of the Budget may adjust a State agency's
37 budgeted receipts to provide an equivalent Labor Market Adjustment Salary Reserve for the
38 2025-2027 fiscal biennium subject to the requirements in subsection (a) of this section, provided
39 that sufficient receipts are available. Agency receipts needed to implement this section are
40 appropriated for the 2025-2026 fiscal year and the 2026-2027 fiscal year.
41 SECTION 41.2A.(c) The Office of State Human Resources (OSHR) shall compile
42 a single report detailing how these funds were distributed by each agency. The OSHR shall
43 develop a uniform reporting mechanism for agencies that displays the salary increases made for
44 each position classification, the average increase provided to employees in each position
45 classification, and the market-based justification for the awarded salary increases. Agencies
46 receiving Labor Market Adjustment Salary Reserve appropriations shall report to the OSHR by
47 December 15, 2025. By January 15, 2026, the OSHR shall submit the report containing the
48 agency responses to the Fiscal Research Division.
