16 by adding a new section to read:
17 "§ 126-14.2A. Hiring candidate from most qualified pool in previous posting.
18 (a) In addition to the authority granted by G.S. 126-3.1, the Council of State, the
19 executive branch agencies, the Community Colleges System Office, and The University of North
20 Carolina are authorized to hire, without posting, into a vacant position if all of the following
21 conditions are met:
22 (1) The employer previously posted for recruitment, in accordance with
23 G.S. 126-7.1 and G.S. 126-14.3, a position that has the same or comparable
24 classification as the position that is currently vacant.
25 (2) The person who is being hired applied for the previous vacant position.
26 (3) The employer selected the person to be in the pool of the most qualified
27 persons for the previous vacant position, in accordance with G.S. 126-14.2,
28 but did not hire that person.
29 (4) For the current vacant position, the person being hired meets the minimum
30 education and experience requirements for the classification and has a salary
31 set within the vacant position's classification range.
32 (b) Except as otherwise provided, the hiring process authorized under this section is
33 exempt from the provisions of this Chapter, including any procedural or substantive requirements
34 such as publicly posting the position, requiring a new application, holding a new interview or
35 conducting new reference checks, and following the priorities for certain types of applicants
36 under State law. This exemption for the hiring process does not affect whether the position is
37 subject to this Chapter once the employee is hired.
38 (c) The hiring process authorized under this section is not exempt from the following
39 provisions of this Chapter:
40 (1) G.S. 126-14.
41 (2) G.S. 126-14.1.
42 (3) G.S. 126-14.5.
43 (4) Article 6.
44 (5) Article 7."
45 SECTION 41.21C.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law.
