19 GRANT EMPLOYING AGENCY FLEXIBILITY/HIRING/PAY/CLASSIFICATION
20 SECTION 41.21E.(a) Article 1 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended
21 by adding a new section to read:
22 "§ 126-3.1. Employing agency flexibility.
23 (a) For the purposes of this section, an "employing agency" means the Council of State,
24 State agencies in the executive branch of government, the Community College System Office,
25 and The University of North Carolina.
26 (b) An employing agency is granted flexibility, notwithstanding other provisions of this
27 Chapter to the contrary, to do all of the following:
28 (1) Offer qualified applicants for employment the option to have their
29 applications considered for future positions at the same agency and at other
30 agencies within the same or comparable classification.
31 (2) Permit agencies to recruit and hire applicants from job postings that apply to
32 all vacancies in a particular classification across all State agencies.
33 (3) Classify or reclassify positions according to the State Human Resources
34 Commission (SHRC) classification system, provided employees meet the
35 minimum requirements for the classification.
36 (4) Establish employee salaries within SHRC-determined salary ranges for
37 respective position classifications.
38 (c) Nothing in this section diminishes the powers of the State Human Resources
39 Commission or the Director of the Office of State Human Resources under any other provision
40 of this Chapter or relating to corrective actions taken when an employing agency fails to comply
41 with this section."
42 SECTION 41.21E.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law or July 1, 2025,
43 whichever is later.
