25 WORK ZONE DYNAMIC SPEED DISPLAY SIGNS
26 SECTION 43.23. Of the funds appropriated from the Highway Fund to the
27 Department of Transportation in this act, one million dollars ($1,000,000) shall be used to
28 purchase dynamic speed display signs and implement their use in highway work zones. For
29 purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
30 (1) Dynamic speed display signs. – A system designed to measure the speed of
31 motor vehicles and alert drivers who are driving in excess of the posted speed
32 limit via flashing lights and a digital message display.
33 (2) Highway work zone. – As defined in G.S. 20-141(j2).
